suncertify.db.server.rmi
Class RMINetworkService

java.lang.Object
  suncertify.db.server.AbstractNetworkService
      suncertify.db.server.rmi.RMINetworkService
All Implemented Interfaces:
NetworkService
public class RMINetworkService
extends AbstractNetworkService

A database network service which uses RMI registry to export engine as a network service.

Database engine interface Engine and related interfaces are mirrored as remote interfaces to be exposed as RMI skeletons which delegates remote requests to wrapped engine, following are each remote interface with related local interface:

  • RemoteEngine will stands off interface Engine
  • RemoteSession will stands off interface Session
  • RemoteDBMain will stands off interface DBMain
all calls for exported skeletons will be navigated to related local instances.
Once this network service is started, a RemoteEngine skeleton will be exported to RMI registry. RemoteSession and RemoteDBMain instances are exported automatically by RMI registry once they are returned through methods calls.
When this network service is stopped, all exported skeletons will be unexported from RMI registry.
The following sample code shows how to access a remote database engine exported to host "host" on port "6666" with name "service1", create a session , then read a data from database:
 
 // get remote engine stub
 RemoteEngine engine = (RemoteEngine) Naming.lookup("//host:6666/service1");
 // create new session
 RemoteSession session = engine.newSession();
 // get data access then read record '0'
 RemoteDBMain dbMain = session.getDataAccess();
 dbMain.read(0);
This network service uses EngineServiceLoader to locate an implementation for EngineService to create an Engine from it to be wrapped by exported skeletons.

Constructor Detail

RMINetworkService

public RMINetworkService(java.io.File databaseFile,
                         java.lang.String serviceName,
                         int port)
                  throws EngineServiceException
Construct a new RMI network service for database file databaseFile.

Network service will be exported to RMI registry on port port with name serviceName. An EngineService instance will be located by EngineServiceLoader to be used as the factory for Engine instance which will manage database file databaseFile, created Engine instance will be wrapped by remote skeletons.

Parameters:
databaseFile - database file to export a network service for.
serviceName - the name to export service with on RMI registry.
port - the port for RMI registry.
Throws:
EngineServiceException

RMINetworkService

public RMINetworkService(EngineService engineService,
                         java.io.File databaseFile,
                         java.lang.String serviceName,
                         int port)
Construct a new RMI network service for database file databaseFile.

Network service will be exported to RMI registry on port port with name serviceName using engine service engineService to create Engine instance for passed database file to be wrapped by exported remote skeletons.

Parameters:
engineService - factory for Engine instance
databaseFile - database file to expose a network service for.
serviceName - the name to export service with on RMI registry.
port - the port for RMI registry.
Method Detail

startSpi

public void startSpi()
              throws NetworkServiceException
Start network service by locating RMI registry and binding engine to it.

Once an Engine instance is created for database file, a skeleton of type RemoteEngine will be exported to RMI registry to accept calls navigated to original local engine instance.

Throws:
NetworkServiceException - if exporting to RMI engine skeleton is failed.

stopSpi

public void stopSpi()
             throws NetworkServiceException
Stop network service by unbinding exported skeletons from RMI registry.

Throws:
NetworkServiceException - if stopping is failed.

getEngine

public Engine getEngine()
Description copied from interface: NetworkService
Returns database engine which this network service is serving.

It may not returns the same engine instance each time called depending on the running status for this service between calls. Best time to call this method after a successful call to NetworkService.start().

Returns:
services database engine instance.
